8725 var globalMap = {
8726   "\\global": "\\global",
8727   "\\long": "\\\\globallong",
8728   "\\\\globallong": "\\\\globallong",
8729   "\\def": "\\gdef",
8730   "\\gdef": "\\gdef",
8731   "\\edef": "\\xdef",
8732   "\\xdef": "\\xdef",
8733   "\\let": "\\\\globallet",
8734   "\\futurelet": "\\\\globalfuture"
8735 };
8736 
8737 var checkControlSequence = tok => {
8738   var name = tok.text;
8739 
8740   if (/^(?:[\\{}$&#^_]|EOF)$/.test(name)) {
8741     throw new ParseError("Expected a control sequence", tok);
8742   }
8743 
8744   return name;
8745 };
8746 
8747 var getRHS = parser => {
8748   var tok = parser.gullet.popToken();
8749 
8750   if (tok.text === "=") {
8751     // consume optional equals
8752     tok = parser.gullet.popToken();
8753 
8754     if (tok.text === " ") {
8755       // consume one optional space
8756       tok = parser.gullet.popToken();
8757     }
8758   }
8759 
8760   return tok;
8761 };
8762 
8763 var letCommand = (parser, name, tok, global) => {
8764   var macro = parser.gullet.macros.get(tok.text);
8765 
8766   if (macro == null) {
8767     // don't expand it later even if a macro with the same name is defined
8768     // e.g., \let\foo=\frac \def\frac{\relax} \frac12
8769     tok.noexpand = true;
8770     macro = {
8771       tokens: [tok],
8772       numArgs: 0,
8773       // reproduce the same behavior in expansion
8774       unexpandable: !parser.gullet.isExpandable(tok.text)
8775     };
8776   }
8777 
8778   parser.gullet.macros.set(name, macro, global);
8779 }; // <assignment> -> <non-macro assignment>|<macro assignment>
8780 // <non-macro assignment> -> <simple assignment>|\global<non-macro assignment>
8781 // <macro assignment> -> <definition>|<prefix><macro assignment>
8782 // <prefix> -> \global|\long|\outer
8783 
8784 
8785 defineFunction({
8786   type: "internal",
8787   names: ["\\global", "\\long", "\\\\globallong" // can’t be entered directly
8788   ],
8789   props: {
8790     numArgs: 0,
8791     allowedInText: true
8792   },
8793 
8794   handler(_ref) {
8795     var {
8796       parser,
8797       funcName
8798     } = _ref;
8799     parser.consumeSpaces();
8800     var token = parser.fetch();
8801 
8802     if (globalMap[token.text]) {
8803       // KaTeX doesn't have \par, so ignore \long
8804       if (funcName === "\\global" || funcName === "\\\\globallong") {
8805         token.text = globalMap[token.text];
8806       }
8807 
8808       return assertNodeType(parser.parseFunction(), "internal");
8809     }
8810 
8811     throw new ParseError("Invalid token after macro prefix", token);
8812   }
8813 
8814 }); // Basic support for macro definitions: \def, \gdef, \edef, \xdef
8815 // <definition> -> <def><control sequence><definition text>
8816 // <def> -> \def|\gdef|\edef|\xdef
8817 // <definition text> -> <parameter text><left brace><balanced text><right brace>
8818 
8819 defineFunction({
8820   type: "internal",
8821   names: ["\\def", "\\gdef", "\\edef", "\\xdef"],
8822   props: {
8823     numArgs: 0,
8824     allowedInText: true,
8825     primitive: true
8826   },
8827 
8828   handler(_ref2) {
8829     var {
8830       parser,
8831       funcName
8832     } = _ref2;
8833     var tok = parser.gullet.popToken();
8834     var name = tok.text;
8835 
8836     if (/^(?:[\\{}$&#^_]|EOF)$/.test(name)) {
8837       throw new ParseError("Expected a control sequence", tok);
8838     }
8839 
8840     var numArgs = 0;
8841     var insert;
8842     var delimiters = [[]]; // <parameter text> contains no braces
8843 
8844     while (parser.gullet.future().text !== "{") {
8845       tok = parser.gullet.popToken();
8846 
8847       if (tok.text === "#") {
8848         // If the very last character of the <parameter text> is #, so that
8849         // this # is immediately followed by {, TeX will behave as if the {
8850         // had been inserted at the right end of both the parameter text
8851         // and the replacement text.
8852         if (parser.gullet.future().text === "{") {
8853           insert = parser.gullet.future();
8854           delimiters[numArgs].push("{");
8855           break;
8856         } // A parameter, the first appearance of # must be followed by 1,
8857         // the next by 2, and so on; up to nine #’s are allowed
8858 
8859 
8860         tok = parser.gullet.popToken();
8861 
8862         if (!/^[1-9]$/.test(tok.text)) {
8863           throw new ParseError("Invalid argument number \"" + tok.text + "\"");
8864         }
8865 
8866         if (parseInt(tok.text) !== numArgs + 1) {
8867           throw new ParseError("Argument number \"" + tok.text + "\" out of order");
8868         }
8869 
8870         numArgs++;
8871         delimiters.push([]);
8872       } else if (tok.text === "EOF") {
8873         throw new ParseError("Expected a macro definition");
8874       } else {
8875         delimiters[numArgs].push(tok.text);
8876       }
8877     } // replacement text, enclosed in '{' and '}' and properly nested
8878 
8879 
8880     var {
8881       tokens
8882     } = parser.gullet.consumeArg();
8883 
8884     if (insert) {
8885       tokens.unshift(insert);
8886     }
8887 
8888     if (funcName === "\\edef" || funcName === "\\xdef") {
8889       tokens = parser.gullet.expandTokens(tokens);
8890       tokens.reverse(); // to fit in with stack order
8891     } // Final arg is the expansion of the macro
8892 
8893 
8894     parser.gullet.macros.set(name, {
8895       tokens,
8896       numArgs,
8897       delimiters
8898     }, funcName === globalMap[funcName]);
8899     return {
8900       type: "internal",
8901       mode: parser.mode
8902     };
8903   }
8904 
8905 }); // <simple assignment> -> <let assignment>
8906 // <let assignment> -> \futurelet<control sequence><token><token>
8907 //     | \let<control sequence><equals><one optional space><token>
8908 // <equals> -> <optional spaces>|<optional spaces>=
8909 
8910 defineFunction({
8911   type: "internal",
8912   names: ["\\let", "\\\\globallet" // can’t be entered directly
8913   ],
8914   props: {
8915     numArgs: 0,
8916     allowedInText: true,
8917     primitive: true
8918   },
8919 
8920   handler(_ref3) {
8921     var {
8922       parser,
8923       funcName
8924     } = _ref3;
8925     var name = checkControlSequence(parser.gullet.popToken());
8926     parser.gullet.consumeSpaces();
8927     var tok = getRHS(parser);
8928     letCommand(parser, name, tok, funcName === "\\\\globallet");
8929     return {
8930       type: "internal",
8931       mode: parser.mode
8932     };
8933   }
8934 
8935 }); // ref: https://www.tug.org/TUGboat/tb09-3/tb22bechtolsheim.pdf

8937 defineFunction({
8938   type: "internal",
8939   names: ["\\futurelet", "\\\\globalfuture" // can’t be entered directly
8940   ],
8941   props: {

8966 /**
8967  * This file deals with creating delimiters of various sizes. The TeXbook
8968  * discusses these routines on page 441-442, in the "Another subroutine sets box
8969  * x to a specified variable delimiter" paragraph.
8970  *
8971  * There are three main routines here. `makeSmallDelim` makes a delimiter in the
8972  * normal font, but in either text, script, or scriptscript style.
8973  * `makeLargeDelim` makes a delimiter in textstyle, but in one of the Size1,
8974  * Size2, Size3, or Size4 fonts. `makeStackedDelim` makes a delimiter out of
8975  * smaller pieces that are stacked on top of one another.
8976  *
8977  * The functions take a parameter `center`, which determines if the delimiter
8978  * should be centered around the axis.
8979  *
8980  * Then, there are three exposed functions. `sizedDelim` makes a delimiter in
8981  * one of the given sizes. This is used for things like `\bigl`.
8982  * `customSizedDelim` makes a delimiter with a given total height+depth. It is
8983  * called in places like `\sqrt`. `leftRightDelim` makes an appropriate
8984  * delimiter which surrounds an expression of a given height an depth. It is
8985  * used in `\left` and `\right`.
8986  */
8987 
8988 /**
8989  * Get the metrics for a given symbol and font, after transformation (i.e.
8990  * after following replacement from symbols.js)
8991  */
8992 var getMetrics = function getMetrics(symbol, font, mode) {
8993   var replace = symbols.math[symbol] && symbols.math[symbol].replace;
8994   var metrics = getCharacterMetrics(replace || symbol, font, mode);
8995 
8996   if (!metrics) {
8997     throw new Error("Unsupported symbol " + symbol + " and font size " + font + ".");
8998   }
8999 
9000   return metrics;
9001 };
9002 /**
9003  * Puts a delimiter span in a given style, and adds appropriate height, depth,
9004  * and maxFontSizes.
9005  */
9006 
9007 
9008 var styleWrap = function styleWrap(delim, toStyle, options, classes) {
9009   var newOptions = options.havingBaseStyle(toStyle);
9010   var span = buildCommon.makeSpan(classes.concat(newOptions.sizingClasses(options)), [delim], options);
9011   var delimSizeMultiplier = newOptions.sizeMultiplier / options.sizeMultiplier;
9012   span.height *= delimSizeMultiplier;
9013   span.depth *= delimSizeMultiplier;
9014   span.maxFontSize = newOptions.sizeMultiplier;
9015   return span;
9016 };
9017 
9018 var centerSpan = function centerSpan(span, options, style) {
9019   var newOptions = options.havingBaseStyle(style);
9020   var shift = (1 - options.sizeMultiplier / newOptions.sizeMultiplier) * options.fontMetrics().axisHeight;
9021   span.classes.push("delimcenter");
9022   span.style.top = makeEm(shift);
9023   span.height -= shift;
9024   span.depth += shift;
9025 };
9026 /**
9027  * Makes a small delimiter. This is a delimiter that comes in the Main-Regular
9028  * font, but is restyled to either be in textstyle, scriptstyle, or
9029  * scriptscriptstyle.
9030  */
9031 
9032 
9033 var makeSmallDelim = function makeSmallDelim(delim, style, center, options, mode, classes) {
9034   var text = buildCommon.makeSymbol(delim, "Main-Regular", mode, options);
9035   var span = styleWrap(text, style, options, classes);
9036 
9037   if (center) {
9038     centerSpan(span, options, style);
9039   }
9040 
9041   return span;
9042 };
9043 /**
9044  * Builds a symbol in the given font size (note size is an integer)
9045  */
9046 
9047 
9048 var mathrmSize = function mathrmSize(value, size, mode, options) {
9049   return buildCommon.makeSymbol(value, "Size" + size + "-Regular", mode, options);
9050 };
9051 /**
9052  * Makes a large delimiter. This is a delimiter that comes in the Size1, Size2,
9053  * Size3, or Size4 fonts. It is always rendered in textstyle.
9054  */
9055 
9056 
9057 var makeLargeDelim = function makeLargeDelim(delim, size, center, options, mode, classes) {
9058   var inner = mathrmSize(delim, size, mode, options);
9059   var span = styleWrap(buildCommon.makeSpan(["delimsizing", "size" + size], [inner], options), Style$1.TEXT, options, classes);
9060 
9061   if (center) {
9062     centerSpan(span, options, Style$1.TEXT);
9063   }
9064 
9065   return span;
9066 };
9067 /**
9068  * Make a span from a font glyph with the given offset and in the given font.
9069  * This is used in makeStackedDelim to make the stacking pieces for the delimiter.
9070  */
9071 
9072 
9073 var makeGlyphSpan = function makeGlyphSpan(symbol, font, mode) {
9074   var sizeClass; // Apply the correct CSS class to choose the right font.
9075 
9076   if (font === "Size1-Regular") {
9077     sizeClass = "delim-size1";
9078   } else
9079     /* if (font === "Size4-Regular") */
9080     {
9081       sizeClass = "delim-size4";
9082     }
9083 
9084   var corner = buildCommon.makeSpan(["delimsizinginner", sizeClass], [buildCommon.makeSpan([], [buildCommon.makeSymbol(symbol, font, mode)])]); // Since this will be passed into `makeVList` in the end, wrap the element
9085   // in the appropriate tag that VList uses.
9086 
9087   return {
9088     type: "elem",
9089     elem: corner
9090   };
9091 };
9092 
9093 var makeInner = function makeInner(ch, height, options) {
9094   // Create a span with inline SVG for the inner part of a tall stacked delimiter.
9095   var width = fontMetricsData['Size4-Regular'][ch.charCodeAt(0)] ? fontMetricsData['Size4-Regular'][ch.charCodeAt(0)][4] : fontMetricsData['Size1-Regular'][ch.charCodeAt(0)][4];
9096   var path = new PathNode("inner", innerPath(ch, Math.round(1000 * height)));
9097   var svgNode = new SvgNode([path], {
9098     "width": makeEm(width),
9099     "height": makeEm(height),
9100     // Override CSS rule `.katex svg { width: 100% }`
9101     "style": "width:" + makeEm(width),
9102     "viewBox": "0 0 " + 1000 * width + " " + Math.round(1000 * height),
9103     "preserveAspectRatio": "xMinYMin"
9104   });
9105   var span = buildCommon.makeSvgSpan([], [svgNode], options);
9106   span.height = height;
9107   span.style.height = makeEm(height);
9108   span.style.width = makeEm(width);
9109   return {
9110     type: "elem",
9111     elem: span
9112   };
9113 }; // Helpers for makeStackedDelim
9114 
9115 
9116 var lapInEms = 0.008;
9117 var lap = {
9118   type: "kern",
9119   size: -1 * lapInEms
9120 };
9121 var verts = ["|", "\\lvert", "\\rvert", "\\vert"];
9122 var doubleVerts = ["\\|", "\\lVert", "\\rVert", "\\Vert"];
9123 /**
9124  * Make a stacked delimiter out of a given delimiter, with the total height at
9125  * least `heightTotal`. This routine is mentioned on page 442 of the TeXbook.
9126  */
9127 
9128 var makeStackedDelim = function makeStackedDelim(delim, heightTotal, center, options, mode, classes) {
9129   // There are four parts, the top, an optional middle, a repeated part, and a
9130   // bottom.
9131   var top;
9132   var middle;
9133   var repeat;
9134   var bottom;
9135   var svgLabel = "";
9136   var viewBoxWidth = 0;
9137   top = repeat = bottom = delim;
9138   middle = null; // Also keep track of what font the delimiters are in
9139 
9140   var font = "Size1-Regular"; // We set the parts and font based on the symbol. Note that we use
9141   // '\u23d0' instead of '|' and '\u2016' instead of '\\|' for the
9142   // repeats of the arrows
9143 
9144   if (delim === "\\uparrow") {
9145     repeat = bottom = "\u23d0";
9146   } else if (delim === "\\Uparrow") {
9147     repeat = bottom = "\u2016";
9148   } else if (delim === "\\downarrow") {
9149     top = repeat = "\u23d0";
9150   } else if (delim === "\\Downarrow") {
9151     top = repeat = "\u2016";
9152   } else if (delim === "\\updownarrow") {
9153     top = "\\uparrow";
9154     repeat = "\u23d0";
9155     bottom = "\\downarrow";
9156   } else if (delim === "\\Updownarrow") {
9157     top = "\\Uparrow";
9158     repeat = "\u2016";
9159     bottom = "\\Downarrow";
9160   } else if (utils.contains(verts, delim)) {
9161     repeat = "\u2223";
9162     svgLabel = "vert";
9163     viewBoxWidth = 333;
9164   } else if (utils.contains(doubleVerts, delim)) {
9165     repeat = "\u2225";
9166     svgLabel = "doublevert";
9167     viewBoxWidth = 556;
9168   } else if (delim === "[" || delim === "\\lbrack") {
9169     top = "\u23a1";
9170     repeat = "\u23a2";
9171     bottom = "\u23a3";
9172     font = "Size4-Regular";
9173     svgLabel = "lbrack";
9174     viewBoxWidth = 667;
9175   } else if (delim === "]" || delim === "\\rbrack") {
9176     top = "\u23a4";
9177     repeat = "\u23a5";
9178     bottom = "\u23a6";
9179     font = "Size4-Regular";
9180     svgLabel = "rbrack";
9181     viewBoxWidth = 667;
9182   } else if (delim === "\\lfloor" || delim === "\u230a") {
9183     repeat = top = "\u23a2";
9184     bottom = "\u23a3";
9185     font = "Size4-Regular";
9186     svgLabel = "lfloor";
9187     viewBoxWidth = 667;
9188   } else if (delim === "\\lceil" || delim === "\u2308") {
9189     top = "\u23a1";
9190     repeat = bottom = "\u23a2";
9191     font = "Size4-Regular";
9192     svgLabel = "lceil";
9193     viewBoxWidth = 667;
9194   } else if (delim === "\\rfloor" || delim === "\u230b") {
9195     repeat = top = "\u23a5";
9196     bottom = "\u23a6";
9197     font = "Size4-Regular";
9198     svgLabel = "rfloor";
9199     viewBoxWidth = 667;
9200   } else if (delim === "\\rceil" || delim === "\u2309") {
9201     top = "\u23a4";
9202     repeat = bottom = "\u23a5";
9203     font = "Size4-Regular";
9204     svgLabel = "rceil";
9205     viewBoxWidth = 667;
9206   } else if (delim === "(" || delim === "\\lparen") {
9207     top = "\u239b";
9208     repeat = "\u239c";
9209     bottom = "\u239d";
9210     font = "Size4-Regular";
9211     svgLabel = "lparen";
9212     viewBoxWidth = 875;
9213   } else if (delim === ")" || delim === "\\rparen") {
9214     top = "\u239e";
9215     repeat = "\u239f";
9216     bottom = "\u23a0";
9217     font = "Size4-Regular";
9218     svgLabel = "rparen";
9219     viewBoxWidth = 875;
9220   } else if (delim === "\\{" || delim === "\\lbrace") {
9221     top = "\u23a7";
9222     middle = "\u23a8";
9223     bottom = "\u23a9";
9224     repeat = "\u23aa";
9225     font = "Size4-Regular";
9226   } else if (delim === "\\}" || delim === "\\rbrace") {
9227     top = "\u23ab";
9228     middle = "\u23ac";
9229     bottom = "\u23ad";
9230     repeat = "\u23aa";
9231     font = "Size4-Regular";
9232   } else if (delim === "\\lgroup" || delim === "\u27ee") {
9233     top = "\u23a7";
9234     bottom = "\u23a9";
9235     repeat = "\u23aa";
9236     font = "Size4-Regular";
9237   } else if (delim === "\\rgroup" || delim === "\u27ef") {
9238     top = "\u23ab";
9239     bottom = "\u23ad";
9240     repeat = "\u23aa";
9241     font = "Size4-Regular";
9242   } else if (delim === "\\lmoustache" || delim === "\u23b0") {
9243     top = "\u23a7";
9244     bottom = "\u23ad";
9245     repeat = "\u23aa";
9246     font = "Size4-Regular";
9247   } else if (delim === "\\rmoustache" || delim === "\u23b1") {
9248     top = "\u23ab";
9249     bottom = "\u23a9";
9250     repeat = "\u23aa";
9251     font = "Size4-Regular";
9252   } // Get the metrics of the four sections
9253 
9254 
9255   var topMetrics = getMetrics(top, font, mode);
9256   var topHeightTotal = topMetrics.height + topMetrics.depth;
9257   var repeatMetrics = getMetrics(repeat, font, mode);
9258   var repeatHeightTotal = repeatMetrics.height + repeatMetrics.depth;
9259   var bottomMetrics = getMetrics(bottom, font, mode);
9260   var bottomHeightTotal = bottomMetrics.height + bottomMetrics.depth;
9261   var middleHeightTotal = 0;
9262   var middleFactor = 1;
9263 
9264   if (middle !== null) {
9265     var middleMetrics = getMetrics(middle, font, mode);
9266     middleHeightTotal = middleMetrics.height + middleMetrics.depth;
9267     middleFactor = 2; // repeat symmetrically above and below middle
9268   } // Calculate the minimal height that the delimiter can have.
9269   // It is at least the size of the top, bottom, and optional middle combined.
9270 
9271 
9272   var minHeight = topHeightTotal + bottomHeightTotal + middleHeightTotal; // Compute the number of copies of the repeat symbol we will need
9273 
9274   var repeatCount = Math.max(0, Math.ceil((heightTotal - minHeight) / (middleFactor * repeatHeightTotal))); // Compute the total height of the delimiter including all the symbols
9275 
9276   var realHeightTotal = minHeight + repeatCount * middleFactor * repeatHeightTotal; // The center of the delimiter is placed at the center of the axis. Note
9277   // that in this context, "center" means that the delimiter should be
9278   // centered around the axis in the current style, while normally it is
9279   // centered around the axis in textstyle.
9280 
9281   var axisHeight = options.fontMetrics().axisHeight;
9282 
9283   if (center) {
9284     axisHeight *= options.sizeMultiplier;
9285   } // Calculate the depth
9286 
9287 
9288   var depth = realHeightTotal / 2 - axisHeight; // Now, we start building the pieces that will go into the vlist
9289   // Keep a list of the pieces of the stacked delimiter
9290 
9291   var stack = [];
9292 
9293   if (svgLabel.length > 0) {
9294     // Instead of stacking glyphs, create a single SVG.
9295     // This evades browser problems with imprecise positioning of spans.
9296     var midHeight = realHeightTotal - topHeightTotal - bottomHeightTotal;
9297     var viewBoxHeight = Math.round(realHeightTotal * 1000);
9298     var pathStr = tallDelim(svgLabel, Math.round(midHeight * 1000));
9299     var path = new PathNode(svgLabel, pathStr);
9300     var width = (viewBoxWidth / 1000).toFixed(3) + "em";
9301     var height = (viewBoxHeight / 1000).toFixed(3) + "em";
9302     var svg = new SvgNode([path], {
9303       "width": width,
9304       "height": height,
9305       "viewBox": "0 0 " + viewBoxWidth + " " + viewBoxHeight
9306     });
9307     var wrapper = buildCommon.makeSvgSpan([], [svg], options);
9308     wrapper.height = viewBoxHeight / 1000;
9309     wrapper.style.width = width;
9310     wrapper.style.height = height;
9311     stack.push({
9312       type: "elem",
9313       elem: wrapper
9314     });
9315   } else {
9316     // Stack glyphs
9317     // Start by adding the bottom symbol
9318     stack.push(makeGlyphSpan(bottom, font, mode));
9319     stack.push(lap); // overlap
9320 
9321     if (middle === null) {
9322       // The middle section will be an SVG. Make it an extra 0.016em tall.
9323       // We'll overlap by 0.008em at top and bottom.
9324       var innerHeight = realHeightTotal - topHeightTotal - bottomHeightTotal + 2 * lapInEms;
9325       stack.push(makeInner(repeat, innerHeight, options));
9326     } else {
9327       // When there is a middle bit, we need the middle part and two repeated
9328       // sections
9329       var _innerHeight = (realHeightTotal - topHeightTotal - bottomHeightTotal - middleHeightTotal) / 2 + 2 * lapInEms;
9330 
9331       stack.push(makeInner(repeat, _innerHeight, options)); // Now insert the middle of the brace.
9332 
9333       stack.push(lap);
9334       stack.push(makeGlyphSpan(middle, font, mode));
9335       stack.push(lap);
9336       stack.push(makeInner(repeat, _innerHeight, options));
9337     } // Add the top symbol
9338 
9339 
9340     stack.push(lap);
9341     stack.push(makeGlyphSpan(top, font, mode));
9342   } // Finally, build the vlist
9343 
9344 
9345   var newOptions = options.havingBaseStyle(Style$1.TEXT);
9346   var inner = buildCommon.makeVList({
9347     positionType: "bottom",
9348     positionData: depth,
9349     children: stack
9350   }, newOptions);
9351   return styleWrap(buildCommon.makeSpan(["delimsizing", "mult"], [inner], newOptions), Style$1.TEXT, options, classes);
9352 }; // All surds have 0.08em padding above the vinculum inside the SVG.
9353 // That keeps browser span height rounding error from pinching the line.
9354 
9355 
9356 var vbPad = 80; // padding above the surd, measured inside the viewBox.
9357 
9358 var emPad = 0.08; // padding, in ems, measured in the document.
9359 
9360 var sqrtSvg = function sqrtSvg(sqrtName, height, viewBoxHeight, extraVinculum, options) {
9361   var path = sqrtPath(sqrtName, extraVinculum, viewBoxHeight);
9362   var pathNode = new PathNode(sqrtName, path);
9363   var svg = new SvgNode([pathNode], {
9364     // Note: 1000:1 ratio of viewBox to document em width.
9365     "width": "400em",
9366     "height": makeEm(height),
9367     "viewBox": "0 0 400000 " + viewBoxHeight,
9368     "preserveAspectRatio": "xMinYMin slice"
9369   });
9370   return buildCommon.makeSvgSpan(["hide-tail"], [svg], options);
9371 };
9372 /**
9373  * Make a sqrt image of the given height,
9374  */
9375 
9376 
9377 var makeSqrtImage = function makeSqrtImage(height, options) {
9378   // Define a newOptions that removes the effect of size changes such as \Huge.
9379   // We don't pick different a height surd for \Huge. For it, we scale up.
9380   var newOptions = options.havingBaseSizing(); // Pick the desired surd glyph from a sequence of surds.
9381 
9382   var delim = traverseSequence("\\surd", height * newOptions.sizeMultiplier, stackLargeDelimiterSequence, newOptions);
9383   var sizeMultiplier = newOptions.sizeMultiplier; // default
9384   // The standard sqrt SVGs each have a 0.04em thick vinculum.
9385   // If Settings.minRuleThickness is larger than that, we add extraVinculum.
9386 
9387   var extraVinculum = Math.max(0, options.minRuleThickness - options.fontMetrics().sqrtRuleThickness); // Create a span containing an SVG image of a sqrt symbol.
9388 
9389   var span;
9390   var spanHeight = 0;
9391   var texHeight = 0;
9392   var viewBoxHeight = 0;
9393   var advanceWidth; // We create viewBoxes with 80 units of "padding" above each surd.
9394   // Then browser rounding error on the parent span height will not
9395   // encroach on the ink of the vinculum. But that padding is not
9396   // included in the TeX-like `height` used for calculation of
9397   // vertical alignment. So texHeight = span.height < span.style.height.
9398 
9399   if (delim.type === "small") {
9400     // Get an SVG that is derived from glyph U+221A in font KaTeX-Main.
9401     // 1000 unit normal glyph height.
9402     viewBoxHeight = 1000 + 1000 * extraVinculum + vbPad;
9403 
9404     if (height < 1.0) {
9405       sizeMultiplier = 1.0; // mimic a \textfont radical
9406     } else if (height < 1.4) {
9407       sizeMultiplier = 0.7; // mimic a \scriptfont radical
9408     }
9409 
9410     spanHeight = (1.0 + extraVinculum + emPad) / sizeMultiplier;
9411     texHeight = (1.00 + extraVinculum) / sizeMultiplier;
9412     span = sqrtSvg("sqrtMain", spanHeight, viewBoxHeight, extraVinculum, options);
9413     span.style.minWidth = "0.853em";
9414     advanceWidth = 0.833 / sizeMultiplier; // from the font.
9415   } else if (delim.type === "large") {
9416     // These SVGs come from fonts: KaTeX_Size1, _Size2, etc.
9417     viewBoxHeight = (1000 + vbPad) * sizeToMaxHeight[delim.size];
9418     texHeight = (sizeToMaxHeight[delim.size] + extraVinculum) / sizeMultiplier;
9419     spanHeight = (sizeToMaxHeight[delim.size] + extraVinculum + emPad) / sizeMultiplier;
9420     span = sqrtSvg("sqrtSize" + delim.size, spanHeight, viewBoxHeight, extraVinculum, options);
9421     span.style.minWidth = "1.02em";
9422     advanceWidth = 1.0 / sizeMultiplier; // 1.0 from the font.
9423   } else {
9424     // Tall sqrt. In TeX, this would be stacked using multiple glyphs.
9425     // We'll use a single SVG to accomplish the same thing.
9426     spanHeight = height + extraVinculum + emPad;
9427     texHeight = height + extraVinculum;
9428     viewBoxHeight = Math.floor(1000 * height + extraVinculum) + vbPad;
9429     span = sqrtSvg("sqrtTall", spanHeight, viewBoxHeight, extraVinculum, options);
9430     span.style.minWidth = "0.742em";
9431     advanceWidth = 1.056;
9432   }
9433 
9434   span.height = texHeight;
9435   span.style.height = makeEm(spanHeight);
9436   return {
9437     span,
9438     advanceWidth,
9439     // Calculate the actual line width.
9440     // This actually should depend on the chosen font -- e.g. \boldmath
9441     // should use the thicker surd symbols from e.g. KaTeX_Main-Bold, and
9442     // have thicker rules.
9443     ruleWidth: (options.fontMetrics().sqrtRuleThickness + extraVinculum) * sizeMultiplier
9444   };
9445 }; // There are three kinds of delimiters, delimiters that stack when they become
9446 // too large
9447 
9448 
9449 var stackLargeDelimiters = ["(", "\\lparen", ")", "\\rparen", "[", "\\lbrack", "]", "\\rbrack", "\\{", "\\lbrace", "\\}", "\\rbrace", "\\lfloor", "\\rfloor", "\u230a", "\u230b", "\\lceil", "\\rceil", "\u2308", "\u2309", "\\surd"]; // delimiters that always stack
9450 
9451 var stackAlwaysDelimiters = ["\\uparrow", "\\downarrow", "\\updownarrow", "\\Uparrow", "\\Downarrow", "\\Updownarrow", "|", "\\|", "\\vert", "\\Vert", "\\lvert", "\\rvert", "\\lVert", "\\rVert", "\\lgroup", "\\rgroup", "\u27ee", "\u27ef", "\\lmoustache", "\\rmoustache", "\u23b0", "\u23b1"]; // and delimiters that never stack
9452 
9453 var stackNeverDelimiters = ["<", ">", "\\langle", "\\rangle", "/", "\\backslash", "\\lt", "\\gt"]; // Metrics of the different sizes. Found by looking at TeX's output of
9454 // $\bigl| // \Bigl| \biggl| \Biggl| \showlists$
9455 // Used to create stacked delimiters of appropriate sizes in makeSizedDelim.
9456 
9457 var sizeToMaxHeight = [0, 1.2, 1.8, 2.4, 3.0];
9458 /**
9459  * Used to create a delimiter of a specific size, where `size` is 1, 2, 3, or 4.
9460  */
9461 
9462 var makeSizedDelim = function makeSizedDelim(delim, size, options, mode, classes) {
9463   // < and > turn into \langle and \rangle in delimiters
9464   if (delim === "<" || delim === "\\lt" || delim === "\u27e8") {
9465     delim = "\\langle";
9466   } else if (delim === ">" || delim === "\\gt" || delim === "\u27e9") {
9467     delim = "\\rangle";
9468   } // Sized delimiters are never centered.
9469 
9470 
9471   if (utils.contains(stackLargeDelimiters, delim) || utils.contains(stackNeverDelimiters, delim)) {
9472     return makeLargeDelim(delim, size, false, options, mode, classes);
9473   } else if (utils.contains(stackAlwaysDelimiters, delim)) {
9474     return makeStackedDelim(delim, sizeToMaxHeight[size], false, options, mode, classes);
9475   } else {
9476     throw new ParseError("Illegal delimiter: '" + delim + "'");
9477   }
9478 };
9479 /**
9480  * There are three different sequences of delimiter sizes that the delimiters
9481  * follow depending on the kind of delimiter. This is used when creating custom
9482  * sized delimiters to decide whether to create a small, large, or stacked
9483  * delimiter.
9484  *
9485  * In real TeX, these sequences aren't explicitly defined, but are instead
9486  * defined inside the font metrics. Since there are only three sequences that
9487  * are possible for the delimiters that TeX defines, it is easier to just encode
9488  * them explicitly here.
9489  */
9490 
9491 
9492 // Delimiters that never stack try small delimiters and large delimiters only
9493 var stackNeverDelimiterSequence = [{
9494   type: "small",
9495   style: Style$1.SCRIPTSCRIPT
9496 }, {
9497   type: "small",
9498   style: Style$1.SCRIPT
9499 }, {
9500   type: "small",
9501   style: Style$1.TEXT
9502 }, {
9503   type: "large",
9504   size: 1
9505 }, {
9506   type: "large",
9507   size: 2
9508 }, {
9509   type: "large",
9510   size: 3
9511 }, {
9512   type: "large",
9513   size: 4
9514 }]; // Delimiters that always stack try the small delimiters first, then stack
9515 
9516 var stackAlwaysDelimiterSequence = [{
9517   type: "small",
9518   style: Style$1.SCRIPTSCRIPT
9519 }, {
9520   type: "small",
9521   style: Style$1.SCRIPT
9522 }, {
9523   type: "small",
9524   style: Style$1.TEXT
9525 }, {
9526   type: "stack"
9527 }]; // Delimiters that stack when large try the small and then large delimiters, and
9528 // stack afterwards
9529 
9530 var stackLargeDelimiterSequence = [{
9531   type: "small",
9532   style: Style$1.SCRIPTSCRIPT
9533 }, {
9534   type: "small",
9535   style: Style$1.SCRIPT
9536 }, {
9537   type: "small",
9538   style: Style$1.TEXT
9539 }, {
9540   type: "large",
9541   size: 1
9542 }, {
9543   type: "large",
9544   size: 2
9545 }, {
9546   type: "large",
9547   size: 3
9548 }, {
9549   type: "large",
9550   size: 4
9551 }, {
9552   type: "stack"
9553 }];
9554 /**
9555  * Get the font used in a delimiter based on what kind of delimiter it is.
9556  * TODO(#963) Use more specific font family return type once that is introduced.
9557  */
9558 
9559 var delimTypeToFont = function delimTypeToFont(type) {
9560   if (type.type === "small") {
9561     return "Main-Regular";
9562   } else if (type.type === "large") {
9563     return "Size" + type.size + "-Regular";
9564   } else if (type.type === "stack") {
9565     return "Size4-Regular";
9566   } else {
9567     throw new Error("Add support for delim type '" + type.type + "' here.");
9568   }
9569 };
9570 /**
9571  * Traverse a sequence of types of delimiters to decide what kind of delimiter
9572  * should be used to create a delimiter of the given height+depth.
9573  */
9574 
9575 
9576 var traverseSequence = function traverseSequence(delim, height, sequence, options) {
9577   // Here, we choose the index we should start at in the sequences. In smaller
9578   // sizes (which correspond to larger numbers in style.size) we start earlier
9579   // in the sequence. Thus, scriptscript starts at index 3-3=0, script starts
9580   // at index 3-2=1, text starts at 3-1=2, and display starts at min(2,3-0)=2
9581   var start = Math.min(2, 3 - options.style.size);
9582 
9583   for (var i = start; i < sequence.length; i++) {
9584     if (sequence[i].type === "stack") {
9585       // This is always the last delimiter, so we just break the loop now.
9586       break;
9587     }
9588 
9589     var metrics = getMetrics(delim, delimTypeToFont(sequence[i]), "math");
9590     var heightDepth = metrics.height + metrics.depth; // Small delimiters are scaled down versions of the same font, so we
9591     // account for the style change size.
9592 
9593     if (sequence[i].type === "small") {
9594       var newOptions = options.havingBaseStyle(sequence[i].style);
9595       heightDepth *= newOptions.sizeMultiplier;
9596     } // Check if the delimiter at this size works for the given height.
9597 
9598 
9599     if (heightDepth > height) {
9600       return sequence[i];
9601     }
9602   } // If we reached the end of the sequence, return the last sequence element.
9603 
9604 
9605   return sequence[sequence.length - 1];
9606 };
9607 /**
9608  * Make a delimiter of a given height+depth, with optional centering. Here, we
9609  * traverse the sequences, and create a delimiter that the sequence tells us to.
9610  */
9611 
9612 
9613 var makeCustomSizedDelim = function makeCustomSizedDelim(delim, height, center, options, mode, classes) {
9614   if (delim === "<" || delim === "\\lt" || delim === "\u27e8") {
9615     delim = "\\langle";
9616   } else if (delim === ">" || delim === "\\gt" || delim === "\u27e9") {
9617     delim = "\\rangle";
9618   } // Decide what sequence to use
9619 
9620 
9621   var sequence;
9622 
9623   if (utils.contains(stackNeverDelimiters, delim)) {
9624     sequence = stackNeverDelimiterSequence;
9625   } else if (utils.contains(stackLargeDelimiters, delim)) {
9626     sequence = stackLargeDelimiterSequence;
9627   } else {
9628     sequence = stackAlwaysDelimiterSequence;
9629   } // Look through the sequence
9630 
9631 
9632   var delimType = traverseSequence(delim, height, sequence, options); // Get the delimiter from font glyphs.
9633   // Depending on the sequence element we decided on, call the
9634   // appropriate function.
9635 
9636   if (delimType.type === "small") {
9637     return makeSmallDelim(delim, delimType.style, center, options, mode, classes);
9638   } else if (delimType.type === "large") {
9639     return makeLargeDelim(delim, delimType.size, center, options, mode, classes);
9640   } else
9641     /* if (delimType.type === "stack") */
9642     {
9643       return makeStackedDelim(delim, height, center, options, mode, classes);
9644     }
9645 };
9646 /**
9647  * Make a delimiter for use with `\left` and `\right`, given a height and depth
9648  * of an expression that the delimiters surround.
9649  */
9650 
9651 
9652 var makeLeftRightDelim = function makeLeftRightDelim(delim, height, depth, options, mode, classes) {
9653   // We always center \left/\right delimiters, so the axis is always shifted
9654   var axisHeight = options.fontMetrics().axisHeight * options.sizeMultiplier; // Taken from TeX source, tex.web, function make_left_right
9655 
9656   var delimiterFactor = 901;
9657   var delimiterExtend = 5.0 / options.fontMetrics().ptPerEm;
9658   var maxDistFromAxis = Math.max(height - axisHeight, depth + axisHeight);
9659   var totalHeight = Math.max( // In real TeX, calculations are done using integral values which are
9660   // 65536 per pt, or 655360 per em. So, the division here truncates in
9661   // TeX but doesn't here, producing different results. If we wanted to
9662   // exactly match TeX's calculation, we could do
9663   //   Math.floor(655360 * maxDistFromAxis / 500) *
9664   //    delimiterFactor / 655360
9665   // (To see the difference, compare
9666   //    x^{x^{\left(\rule{0.1em}{0.68em}\right)}}
9667   // in TeX and KaTeX)
9668   maxDistFromAxis / 500 * delimiterFactor, 2 * maxDistFromAxis - delimiterExtend); // Finally, we defer to `makeCustomSizedDelim` with our calculated total
9669   // height
9670 
9671   return makeCustomSizedDelim(delim, totalHeight, true, options, mode, classes);
9672 };

9677   sizeToMaxHeight: sizeToMaxHeight,
9678   customSizedDelim: makeCustomSizedDelim,
9679   leftRightDelim: makeLeftRightDelim
9680 };

9749 var delimiters = ["(", "\\lparen", ")", "\\rparen", "[", "\\lbrack", "]", "\\rbrack", "\\{", "\\lbrace", "\\}", "\\rbrace", "\\lfloor", "\\rfloor", "\u230a", "\u230b", "\\lceil", "\\rceil", "\u2308", "\u2309", "<", ">", "\\langle", "\u27e8", "\\rangle", "\u27e9", "\\lt", "\\gt", "\\lvert", "\\rvert", "\\lVert", "\\rVert", "\\lgroup", "\\rgroup", "\u27ee", "\u27ef", "\\lmoustache", "\\rmoustache", "\u23b0", "\u23b1", "/", "\\backslash", "|", "\\vert", "\\|", "\\Vert", "\\uparrow", "\\Uparrow", "\\downarrow", "\\Downarrow", "\\updownarrow", "\\Updownarrow", "."];

9751 // Delimiter functions
9752 function checkDelimiter(delim, context) {
9753   var symDelim = checkSymbolNodeType(delim);
9754 
9755   if (symDelim && utils.contains(delimiters, symDelim.text)) {
9756     return symDelim;
9757   } else if (symDelim) {
9758     throw new ParseError("Invalid delimiter '" + symDelim.text + "' after '" + context.funcName + "'", delim);
9759   } else {
9760     throw new ParseError("Invalid delimiter type '" + delim.type + "'", delim);
9761   }
9762 }

9764 defineFunction({
9765   type: "delimsizing",
9766   names: ["\\bigl", "\\Bigl", "\\biggl", "\\Biggl", "\\bigr", "\\Bigr", "\\biggr", "\\Biggr", "\\bigm", "\\Bigm", "\\biggm", "\\Biggm", "\\big", "\\Big", "\\bigg", "\\Bigg"],
9767   props: {
9768     numArgs: 1,
9769     argTypes: ["primitive"]
9770   },
9771   handler: (context, args) => {
9772     var delim = checkDelimiter(args[0], context);
9773     return {
9774       type: "delimsizing",
9775       mode: context.parser.mode,
9776       size: delimiterSizes[context.funcName].size,
9777       mclass: delimiterSizes[context.funcName].mclass,
9778       delim: delim.text
9779     };
9780   },
9781   htmlBuilder: (group, options) => {
9782     if (group.delim === ".") {
9783       // Empty delimiters still count as elements, even though they don't
9784       // show anything.
9785       return buildCommon.makeSpan([group.mclass]);
9786     } // Use delimiter.sizedDelim to generate the delimiter.
9787 
9788 
9789     return delimiter.sizedDelim(group.delim, group.size, options, group.mode, [group.mclass]);
9790   },
9791   mathmlBuilder: group => {
9792     var children = [];
9793 
9794     if (group.delim !== ".") {
9795       children.push(makeText(group.delim, group.mode));
9796     }
9797 
9798     var node = new mathMLTree.MathNode("mo", children);
9799 
9800     if (group.mclass === "mopen" || group.mclass === "mclose") {
9801       // Only some of the delimsizing functions act as fences, and they
9802       // return "mopen" or "mclose" mclass.
9803       node.setAttribute("fence", "true");
9804     } else {
9805       // Explicitly disable fencing if it's not a fence, to override the
9806       // defaults.
9807       node.setAttribute("fence", "false");
9808     }
9809 
9810     node.setAttribute("stretchy", "true");
9811     var size = makeEm(delimiter.sizeToMaxHeight[group.size]);
9812     node.setAttribute("minsize", size);
9813     node.setAttribute("maxsize", size);
9814     return node;
9815   }
9816 });

9818 function assertParsed(group) {
9819   if (!group.body) {
9820     throw new Error("Bug: The leftright ParseNode wasn't fully parsed.");
9821   }
9822 }

9824 defineFunction({
9825   type: "leftright-right",
9826   names: ["\\right"],
9827   props: {
9828     numArgs: 1,
9829     primitive: true
9830   },
9831   handler: (context, args) => {
9832     // \left case below triggers parsing of \right in
9833     //   `const right = parser.parseFunction();`
9834     // uses this return value.
9835     var color = context.parser.gullet.macros.get("\\current@color");
9836 
9837     if (color && typeof color !== "string") {
9838       throw new ParseError("\\current@color set to non-string in \\right");
9839     }
9840 
9841     return {
9842       type: "leftright-right",
9843       mode: context.parser.mode,
9844       delim: checkDelimiter(args[0], context).text,
9845       color // undefined if not set via \color
9846 
9847     };
9848   }
9849 });
9850 defineFunction({
9851   type: "leftright",
9852   names: ["\\left"],
9853   props: {
9854     numArgs: 1,
9855     primitive: true
9856   },
9857   handler: (context, args) => {
9858     var delim = checkDelimiter(args[0], context);
9859     var parser = context.parser; // Parse out the implicit body
9860 
9861     ++parser.leftrightDepth; // parseExpression stops before '\\right'
9862 
9863     var body = parser.parseExpression(false);
9864     --parser.leftrightDepth; // Check the next token
9865 
9866     parser.expect("\\right", false);
9867     var right = assertNodeType(parser.parseFunction(), "leftright-right");
9868     return {
9869       type: "leftright",
9870       mode: parser.mode,
9871       body,
9872       left: delim.text,
9873       right: right.delim,
9874       rightColor: right.color
9875     };
9876   },
9877   htmlBuilder: (group, options) => {
9878     assertParsed(group); // Build the inner expression
9879 
9880     var inner = buildExpression$1(group.body, options, true, ["mopen", "mclose"]);
9881     var innerHeight = 0;
9882     var innerDepth = 0;
9883     var hadMiddle = false; // Calculate its height and depth
9884 
9885     for (var i = 0; i < inner.length; i++) {
9886       // Property `isMiddle` not defined on `span`. See comment in
9887       // "middle"'s htmlBuilder.
9888       // $FlowFixMe
9889       if (inner[i].isMiddle) {
9890         hadMiddle = true;
9891       } else {
9892         innerHeight = Math.max(inner[i].height, innerHeight);
9893         innerDepth = Math.max(inner[i].depth, innerDepth);
9894       }
9895     } // The size of delimiters is the same, regardless of what style we are
9896     // in. Thus, to correctly calculate the size of delimiter we need around
9897     // a group, we scale down the inner size based on the size.
9898 
9899 
9900     innerHeight *= options.sizeMultiplier;
9901     innerDepth *= options.sizeMultiplier;
9902     var leftDelim;
9903 
9904     if (group.left === ".") {
9905       // Empty delimiters in \left and \right make null delimiter spaces.
9906       leftDelim = makeNullDelimiter(options, ["mopen"]);
9907     } else {
9908       // Otherwise, use leftRightDelim to generate the correct sized
9909       // delimiter.
9910       leftDelim = delimiter.leftRightDelim(group.left, innerHeight, innerDepth, options, group.mode, ["mopen"]);
9911     } // Add it to the beginning of the expression
9912 
9913 
9914     inner.unshift(leftDelim); // Handle middle delimiters
9915 
9916     if (hadMiddle) {
9917       for (var _i = 1; _i < inner.length; _i++) {
9918         var middleDelim = inner[_i]; // Property `isMiddle` not defined on `span`. See comment in
9919         // "middle"'s htmlBuilder.
9920         // $FlowFixMe
9921 
9922         var isMiddle = middleDelim.isMiddle;
9923 
9924         if (isMiddle) {
9925           // Apply the options that were active when \middle was called
9926           inner[_i] = delimiter.leftRightDelim(isMiddle.delim, innerHeight, innerDepth, isMiddle.options, group.mode, []);
9927         }
9928       }
9929     }
9930 
9931     var rightDelim; // Same for the right delimiter, but using color specified by \color
9932 
9933     if (group.right === ".") {
9934       rightDelim = makeNullDelimiter(options, ["mclose"]);
9935     } else {
9936       var colorOptions = group.rightColor ? options.withColor(group.rightColor) : options;
9937       rightDelim = delimiter.leftRightDelim(group.right, innerHeight, innerDepth, colorOptions, group.mode, ["mclose"]);
9938     } // Add it to the end of the expression.
9939 
9940 
9941     inner.push(rightDelim);
9942     return buildCommon.makeSpan(["minner"], inner, options);
9943   },
9944   mathmlBuilder: (group, options) => {
9945     assertParsed(group);
9946     var inner = buildExpression(group.body, options);
9947 
9948     if (group.left !== ".") {
9949       var leftNode = new mathMLTree.MathNode("mo", [makeText(group.left, group.mode)]);
9950       leftNode.setAttribute("fence", "true");
9951       inner.unshift(leftNode);
9952     }
9953 
9954     if (group.right !== ".") {
9955       var rightNode = new mathMLTree.MathNode("mo", [makeText(group.right, group.mode)]);
9956       rightNode.setAttribute("fence", "true");
9957 
9958       if (group.rightColor) {
9959         rightNode.setAttribute("mathcolor", group.rightColor);
9960       }
9961 
9962       inner.push(rightNode);
9963     }
9964 
9965     return makeRow(inner);
9966   }
9967 });
9968 defineFunction({
9969   type: "middle",
9970   names: ["\\middle"],
9971   props: {
9972     numArgs: 1,
9973     primitive: true
9974   },
9975   handler: (context, args) => {
9976     var delim = checkDelimiter(args[0], context);
9977 
9978     if (!context.parser.leftrightDepth) {
9979       throw new ParseError("\\middle without preceding \\left", delim);
9980     }
9981 
9982     return {
9983       type: "middle",
9984       mode: context.parser.mode,
9985       delim: delim.text
9986     };
9987   },
9988   htmlBuilder: (group, options) => {
9989     var middleDelim;
9990 
9991     if (group.delim === ".") {
9992       middleDelim = makeNullDelimiter(options, []);
9993     } else {
9994       middleDelim = delimiter.sizedDelim(group.delim, 1, options, group.mode, []);
9995       var isMiddle = {
9996         delim: group.delim,
9997         options
9998       }; // Property `isMiddle` not defined on `span`. It is only used in
9999       // this file above.
10000       // TODO: Fix this violation of the `span` type and possibly rename
10001       // things since `isMiddle` sounds like a boolean, but is a struct.
10002       // $FlowFixMe
10003 
10004       middleDelim.isMiddle = isMiddle;
10005     }
10006 
10007     return middleDelim;
10008   },
10009   mathmlBuilder: (group, options) => {
10010     // A Firefox \middle will stretch a character vertically only if it
10011     // is in the fence part of the operator dictionary at:
10012     // https://www.w3.org/TR/MathML3/appendixc.html.
10013     // So we need to avoid U+2223 and use plain "|" instead.
10014     var textNode = group.delim === "\\vert" || group.delim === "|" ? makeText("|", "text") : makeText(group.delim, group.mode);
10015     var middleNode = new mathMLTree.MathNode("mo", [textNode]);
10016     middleNode.setAttribute("fence", "true"); // MathML gives 5/18em spacing to each <mo> element.
10017     // \middle should get delimiter spacing instead.
10018 
10019     middleNode.setAttribute("lspace", "0.05em");
10020     middleNode.setAttribute("rspace", "0.05em");
10021     return middleNode;
10022   }
10023 });
10024 
10025 var htmlBuilder$7 = (group, options) => {
10026   // \cancel, \bcancel, \xcancel, \sout, \fbox, \colorbox, \fcolorbox, \phase
10027   // Some groups can return document fragments.  Handle those by wrapping
10028   // them in a span.
10029   var inner = buildCommon.wrapFragment(buildGroup$1(group.body, options), options);
10030   var label = group.label.slice(1);
10031   var scale = options.sizeMultiplier;
10032   var img;
10033   var imgShift = 0; // In the LaTeX cancel package, line geometry is slightly different
10034   // depending on whether the subject is wider than it is tall, or vice versa.
10035   // We don't know the width of a group, so as a proxy, we test if
10036   // the subject is a single character. This captures most of the
10037   // subjects that should get the "tall" treatment.
10038 
10039   var isSingleChar = utils.isCharacterBox(group.body);
10040 
10041   if (label === "sout") {
10042     img = buildCommon.makeSpan(["stretchy", "sout"]);
10043     img.height = options.fontMetrics().defaultRuleThickness / scale;
10044     imgShift = -0.5 * options.fontMetrics().xHeight;
10045   } else if (label === "phase") {
10046     // Set a couple of dimensions from the steinmetz package.
10047     var lineWeight = calculateSize({
10048       number: 0.6,
10049       unit: "pt"
10050     }, options);
10051     var clearance = calculateSize({
10052       number: 0.35,
10053       unit: "ex"
10054     }, options); // Prevent size changes like \Huge from affecting line thickness
10055 
10056     var newOptions = options.havingBaseSizing();
10057     scale = scale / newOptions.sizeMultiplier;
10058     var angleHeight = inner.height + inner.depth + lineWeight + clearance; // Reserve a left pad for the angle.
10059 
10060     inner.style.paddingLeft = makeEm(angleHeight / 2 + lineWeight); // Create an SVG
10061 
10062     var viewBoxHeight = Math.floor(1000 * angleHeight * scale);
10063     var path = phasePath(viewBoxHeight);
10064     var svgNode = new SvgNode([new PathNode("phase", path)], {
10065       "width": "400em",
10066       "height": makeEm(viewBoxHeight / 1000),
10067       "viewBox": "0 0 400000 " + viewBoxHeight,
10068       "preserveAspectRatio": "xMinYMin slice"
10069     }); // Wrap it in a span with overflow: hidden.
10070 
10071     img = buildCommon.makeSvgSpan(["hide-tail"], [svgNode], options);
10072     img.style.height = makeEm(angleHeight);
10073     imgShift = inner.depth + lineWeight + clearance;
10074   } else {
10075     // Add horizontal padding
10076     if (/cancel/.test(label)) {
10077       if (!isSingleChar) {
10078         inner.classes.push("cancel-pad");
10079       }
10080     } else if (label === "angl") {
10081       inner.classes.push("anglpad");
10082     } else {
10083       inner.classes.push("boxpad");
10084     } // Add vertical padding
10085 
10086 
10087     var topPad = 0;
10088     var bottomPad = 0;
10089     var ruleThickness = 0; // ref: cancel package: \advance\totalheight2\p@ % "+2"
10090 
10091     if (/box/.test(label)) {
10092       ruleThickness = Math.max(options.fontMetrics().fboxrule, // default
10093       options.minRuleThickness // User override.
10094       );
10095       topPad = options.fontMetrics().fboxsep + (label === "colorbox" ? 0 : ruleThickness);
10096       bottomPad = topPad;
10097     } else if (label === "angl") {
10098       ruleThickness = Math.max(options.fontMetrics().defaultRuleThickness, options.minRuleThickness);
10099       topPad = 4 * ruleThickness; // gap = 3 × line, plus the line itself.
10100 
10101       bottomPad = Math.max(0, 0.25 - inner.depth);
10102     } else {
10103       topPad = isSingleChar ? 0.2 : 0;
10104       bottomPad = topPad;
10105     }
10106 
10107     img = stretchy.encloseSpan(inner, label, topPad, bottomPad, options);
10108 
10109     if (/fbox|boxed|fcolorbox/.test(label)) {
10110       img.style.borderStyle = "solid";
10111       img.style.borderWidth = makeEm(ruleThickness);
10112     } else if (label === "angl" && ruleThickness !== 0.049) {
10113       img.style.borderTopWidth = makeEm(ruleThickness);
10114       img.style.borderRightWidth = makeEm(ruleThickness);
10115     }
10116 
10117     imgShift = inner.depth + bottomPad;
10118 
10119     if (group.backgroundColor) {
10120       img.style.backgroundColor = group.backgroundColor;
10121 
10122       if (group.borderColor) {
10123         img.style.borderColor = group.borderColor;
10124       }
10125     }
10126   }
10127 
10128   var vlist;
10129 
10130   if (group.backgroundColor) {
10131     vlist = buildCommon.makeVList({
10132       positionType: "individualShift",
10133       children: [// Put the color background behind inner;
10134       {
10135         type: "elem",
10136         elem: img,
10137         shift: imgShift
10138       }, {
10139         type: "elem",
10140         elem: inner,
10141         shift: 0
10142       }]
10143     }, options);
10144   } else {
10145     var classes = /cancel|phase/.test(label) ? ["svg-align"] : [];
10146     vlist = buildCommon.makeVList({
10147       positionType: "individualShift",
10148       children: [// Write the \cancel stroke on top of inner.
10149       {
10150         type: "elem",
10151         elem: inner,
10152         shift: 0
10153       }, {
10154         type: "elem",
10155         elem: img,
10156         shift: imgShift,
10157         wrapperClasses: classes
10158       }]
10159     }, options);
10160   }
10161 
10162   if (/cancel/.test(label)) {
10163     // The cancel package documentation says that cancel lines add their height
10164     // to the expression, but tests show that isn't how it actually works.
10165     vlist.height = inner.height;
10166     vlist.depth = inner.depth;
10167   }
10168 
10169   if (/cancel/.test(label) && !isSingleChar) {
10170     // cancel does not create horiz space for its line extension.
10171     return buildCommon.makeSpan(["mord", "cancel-lap"], [vlist], options);
10172   } else {
10173     return buildCommon.makeSpan(["mord"], [vlist], options);
10174   }
10175 };

10177 var mathmlBuilder$6 = (group, options) => {
10178   var fboxsep = 0;
10179   var node = new mathMLTree.MathNode(group.label.indexOf("colorbox") > -1 ? "mpadded" : "menclose", [buildGroup(group.body, options)]);
10180 
10181   switch (group.label) {
10182     case "\\cancel":
10183       node.setAttribute("notation", "updiagonalstrike");
10184       break;
10185 
10186     case "\\bcancel":
10187       node.setAttribute("notation", "downdiagonalstrike");
10188       break;
10189 
10190     case "\\phase":
10191       node.setAttribute("notation", "phasorangle");
10192       break;
10193 
10194     case "\\sout":
10195       node.setAttribute("notation", "horizontalstrike");
10196       break;
10197 
10198     case "\\fbox":
10199       node.setAttribute("notation", "box");
10200       break;
10201 
10202     case "\\angl":
10203       node.setAttribute("notation", "actuarial");
10204       break;
10205 
10206     case "\\fcolorbox":
10207     case "\\colorbox":
10208       // <menclose> doesn't have a good notation option. So use <mpadded>
10209       // instead. Set some attributes that come included with <menclose>.
10210       fboxsep = options.fontMetrics().fboxsep * options.fontMetrics().ptPerEm;
10211       node.setAttribute("width", "+" + 2 * fboxsep + "pt");
10212       node.setAttribute("height", "+" + 2 * fboxsep + "pt");
10213       node.setAttribute("lspace", fboxsep + "pt"); //
10214 
10215       node.setAttribute("voffset", fboxsep + "pt");
10216 
10217       if (group.label === "\\fcolorbox") {
10218         var thk = Math.max(options.fontMetrics().fboxrule, // default
10219         options.minRuleThickness // user override
10220         );
10221         node.setAttribute("style", "border: " + thk + "em solid " + String(group.borderColor));
10222       }
10223 
10224       break;
10225 
10226     case "\\xcancel":
10227       node.setAttribute("notation", "updiagonalstrike downdiagonalstrike");
10228       break;
10229   }
10230 
10231   if (group.backgroundColor) {
10232     node.setAttribute("mathbackground", group.backgroundColor);
10233   }
10234 
10235   return node;
10236 };

10416 // Helper functions
10417 function getHLines(parser) {
10418   // Return an array. The array length = number of hlines.
10419   // Each element in the array tells if the line is dashed.
10420   var hlineInfo = [];
10421   parser.consumeSpaces();
10422   var nxt = parser.fetch().text;
10423 
10424   if (nxt === "\\relax") {
10425     // \relax is an artifact of the \cr macro below
10426     parser.consume();
10427     parser.consumeSpaces();
10428     nxt = parser.fetch().text;
10429   }
10430 
10431   while (nxt === "\\hline" || nxt === "\\hdashline") {
10432     parser.consume();
10433     hlineInfo.push(nxt === "\\hdashline");
10434     parser.consumeSpaces();
10435     nxt = parser.fetch().text;
10436   }
10437 
10438   return hlineInfo;
10439 }

10460 /**
10461  * Parse the body of the environment, with rows delimited by \\ and
10462  * columns delimited by &, and create a nested list in row-major order
10463  * with one group per cell.  If given an optional argument style
10464  * ("text", "display", etc.), then each cell is cast into that style.
10465  */
10466 
10467 
10468 function parseArray(parser, _ref, style) {
10469   var {
10470     hskipBeforeAndAfter,
10471     addJot,
10472     cols,
10473     arraystretch,
10474     colSeparationType,
10475     autoTag,
10476     singleRow,
10477     emptySingleRow,
10478     maxNumCols,
10479     leqno
10480   } = _ref;
10481   parser.gullet.beginGroup();
10482 
10483   if (!singleRow) {
10484     // \cr is equivalent to \\ without the optional size argument (see below)
10485     // TODO: provide helpful error when \cr is used outside array environment
10486     parser.gullet.macros.set("\\cr", "\\\\\\relax");
10487   } // Get current arraystretch if it's not set by the environment
10488 
10489 
10490   if (!arraystretch) {
10491     var stretch = parser.gullet.expandMacroAsText("\\arraystretch");
10492 
10493     if (stretch == null) {
10494       // Default \arraystretch from lttab.dtx
10495       arraystretch = 1;
10496     } else {
10497       arraystretch = parseFloat(stretch);
10498 
10499       if (!arraystretch || arraystretch < 0) {
10500         throw new ParseError("Invalid \\arraystretch: " + stretch);
10501       }
10502     }
10503   } // Start group for first cell
10504 
10505 
10506   parser.gullet.beginGroup();
10507   var row = [];
10508   var body = [row];
10509   var rowGaps = [];
10510   var hLinesBeforeRow = [];
10511   var tags = autoTag != null ? [] : undefined; // amsmath uses \global\@eqnswtrue and \global\@eqnswfalse to represent
10512   // whether this row should have an equation number.  Simulate this with
10513   // a \@eqnsw macro set to 1 or 0.
10514 
10515   function beginRow() {
10516     if (autoTag) {
10517       parser.gullet.macros.set("\\@eqnsw", "1", true);
10518     }
10519   }
10520 
10521   function endRow() {
10522     if (tags) {
10523       if (parser.gullet.macros.get("\\df@tag")) {
10524         tags.push(parser.subparse([new Token("\\df@tag")]));
10525         parser.gullet.macros.set("\\df@tag", undefined, true);
10526       } else {
10527         tags.push(Boolean(autoTag) && parser.gullet.macros.get("\\@eqnsw") === "1");
10528       }
10529     }
10530   }
10531 
10532   beginRow(); // Test for \hline at the top of the array.
10533 
10534   hLinesBeforeRow.push(getHLines(parser));
10535 
10536   while (true) {
10537     // eslint-disable-line no-constant-condition
10538     // Parse each cell in its own group (namespace)
10539     var cell = parser.parseExpression(false, singleRow ? "\\end" : "\\\\");
10540     parser.gullet.endGroup();
10541     parser.gullet.beginGroup();
10542     cell = {
10543       type: "ordgroup",
10544       mode: parser.mode,
10545       body: cell
10546     };
10547 
10548     if (style) {
10549       cell = {
10550         type: "styling",
10551         mode: parser.mode,
10552         style,
10553         body: [cell]
10554       };
10555     }
10556 
10557     row.push(cell);
10558     var next = parser.fetch().text;
10559 
10560     if (next === "&") {
10561       if (maxNumCols && row.length === maxNumCols) {
10562         if (singleRow || colSeparationType) {
10563           // {equation} or {split}
10564           throw new ParseError("Too many tab characters: &", parser.nextToken);
10565         } else {
10566           // {array} environment
10567           parser.settings.reportNonstrict("textEnv", "Too few columns " + "specified in the {array} column argument.");
10568         }
10569       }
10570 
10571       parser.consume();
10572     } else if (next === "\\end") {
10573       endRow(); // Arrays terminate newlines with `\crcr` which consumes a `\cr` if
10574       // the last line is empty.  However, AMS environments keep the
10575       // empty row if it's the only one.
10576       // NOTE: Currently, `cell` is the last item added into `row`.
10577 
10578       if (row.length === 1 && cell.type === "styling" && cell.body[0].body.length === 0 && (body.length > 1 || !emptySingleRow)) {
10579         body.pop();
10580       }
10581 
10582       if (hLinesBeforeRow.length < body.length + 1) {
10583         hLinesBeforeRow.push([]);
10584       }
10585 
10586       break;
10587     } else if (next === "\\\\") {
10588       parser.consume();
10589       var size = void 0; // \def\Let@{\let\\\math@cr}
10590       // \def\math@cr{...\math@cr@}
10591       // \def\math@cr@{\new@ifnextchar[\math@cr@@{\math@cr@@[\z@]}}
10592       // \def\math@cr@@[#1]{...\math@cr@@@...}
10593       // \def\math@cr@@@{\cr}
10594 
10595       if (parser.gullet.future().text !== " ") {
10596         size = parser.parseSizeGroup(true);
10597       }
10598 
10599       rowGaps.push(size ? size.value : null);
10600       endRow(); // check for \hline(s) following the row separator
10601 
10602       hLinesBeforeRow.push(getHLines(parser));
10603       row = [];
10604       body.push(row);
10605       beginRow();
10606     } else {
10607       throw new ParseError("Expected & or \\\\ or \\cr or \\end", parser.nextToken);
10608     }
10609   } // End cell group
10610 
10611 
10612   parser.gullet.endGroup(); // End array group defining \cr
10613 
10614   parser.gullet.endGroup();
10615   return {
10616     type: "array",
10617     mode: parser.mode,
10618     addJot,
10619     arraystretch,
10620     body,
10621     cols,
10622     rowGaps,
10623     hskipBeforeAndAfter,
10624     hLinesBeforeRow,
10625     colSeparationType,
10626     tags,
10627     leqno
10628   };
10629 } // Decides on a style for cells in an array according to whether the given
10630 // environment name starts with the letter 'd'.
10631 
10632 
10633 function dCellStyle(envName) {
10634   if (envName.slice(0, 1) === "d") {
10635     return "display";
10636   } else {
10637     return "text";
10638   }
10639 }

10641 var htmlBuilder$6 = function htmlBuilder(group, options) {
10642   var r;
10643   var c;
10644   var nr = group.body.length;
10645   var hLinesBeforeRow = group.hLinesBeforeRow;
10646   var nc = 0;
10647   var body = new Array(nr);
10648   var hlines = [];
10649   var ruleThickness = Math.max( // From LaTeX \showthe\arrayrulewidth. Equals 0.04 em.
10650   options.fontMetrics().arrayRuleWidth, options.minRuleThickness // User override.
10651   ); // Horizontal spacing
10652 
10653   var pt = 1 / options.fontMetrics().ptPerEm;
10654   var arraycolsep = 5 * pt; // default value, i.e. \arraycolsep in article.cls
10655 
10656   if (group.colSeparationType && group.colSeparationType === "small") {
10657     // We're in a {smallmatrix}. Default column space is \thickspace,
10658     // i.e. 5/18em = 0.2778em, per amsmath.dtx for {smallmatrix}.
10659     // But that needs adjustment because LaTeX applies \scriptstyle to the
10660     // entire array, including the colspace, but this function applies
10661     // \scriptstyle only inside each element.
10662     var localMultiplier = options.havingStyle(Style$1.SCRIPT).sizeMultiplier;
10663     arraycolsep = 0.2778 * (localMultiplier / options.sizeMultiplier);
10664   } // Vertical spacing
10665 
10666 
10667   var baselineskip = group.colSeparationType === "CD" ? calculateSize({
10668     number: 3,
10669     unit: "ex"
10670   }, options) : 12 * pt; // see size10.clo
10671   // Default \jot from ltmath.dtx
10672   // TODO(edemaine): allow overriding \jot via \setlength (#687)
10673 
10674   var jot = 3 * pt;
10675   var arrayskip = group.arraystretch * baselineskip;
10676   var arstrutHeight = 0.7 * arrayskip; // \strutbox in ltfsstrc.dtx and
10677 
10678   var arstrutDepth = 0.3 * arrayskip; // \@arstrutbox in lttab.dtx
10679 
10680   var totalHeight = 0; // Set a position for \hline(s) at the top of the array, if any.
10681 
10682   function setHLinePos(hlinesInGap) {
10683     for (var i = 0; i < hlinesInGap.length; ++i) {
10684       if (i > 0) {
10685         totalHeight += 0.25;
10686       }
10687 
10688       hlines.push({
10689         pos: totalHeight,
10690         isDashed: hlinesInGap[i]
10691       });
10692     }
10693   }
10694 
10695   setHLinePos(hLinesBeforeRow[0]);
10696 
10697   for (r = 0; r < group.body.length; ++r) {
10698     var inrow = group.body[r];
10699     var height = arstrutHeight; // \@array adds an \@arstrut
10700 
10701     var depth = arstrutDepth; // to each tow (via the template)
10702 
10703     if (nc < inrow.length) {
10704       nc = inrow.length;
10705     }
10706 
10707     var outrow = new Array(inrow.length);
10708 
10709     for (c = 0; c < inrow.length; ++c) {
10710       var elt = buildGroup$1(inrow[c], options);
10711 
10712       if (depth < elt.depth) {
10713         depth = elt.depth;
10714       }
10715 
10716       if (height < elt.height) {
10717         height = elt.height;
10718       }
10719 
10720       outrow[c] = elt;
10721     }
10722 
10723     var rowGap = group.rowGaps[r];
10724     var gap = 0;
10725 
10726     if (rowGap) {
10727       gap = calculateSize(rowGap, options);
10728 
10729       if (gap > 0) {
10730         // \@argarraycr
10731         gap += arstrutDepth;
10732 
10733         if (depth < gap) {
10734           depth = gap; // \@xargarraycr
10735         }
10736 
10737         gap = 0;
10738       }
10739     } // In AMS multiline environments such as aligned and gathered, rows
10740     // correspond to lines that have additional \jot added to the
10741     // \baselineskip via \openup.
10742 
10743 
10744     if (group.addJot) {
10745       depth += jot;
10746     }
10747 
10748     outrow.height = height;
10749     outrow.depth = depth;
10750     totalHeight += height;
10751     outrow.pos = totalHeight;
10752     totalHeight += depth + gap; // \@yargarraycr
10753 
10754     body[r] = outrow; // Set a position for \hline(s), if any.
10755 
10756     setHLinePos(hLinesBeforeRow[r + 1]);
10757   }
10758 
10759   var offset = totalHeight / 2 + options.fontMetrics().axisHeight;
10760   var colDescriptions = group.cols || [];
10761   var cols = [];
10762   var colSep;
10763   var colDescrNum;
10764   var tagSpans = [];
10765 
10766   if (group.tags && group.tags.some(tag => tag)) {
10767     // An environment with manual tags and/or automatic equation numbers.
10768     // Create node(s), the latter of which trigger CSS counter increment.
10769     for (r = 0; r < nr; ++r) {
10770       var rw = body[r];
10771       var shift = rw.pos - offset;
10772       var tag = group.tags[r];
10773       var tagSpan = void 0;
10774 
10775       if (tag === true) {
10776         // automatic numbering
10777         tagSpan = buildCommon.makeSpan(["eqn-num"], [], options);
10778       } else if (tag === false) {
10779         // \nonumber/\notag or starred environment
10780         tagSpan = buildCommon.makeSpan([], [], options);
10781       } else {
10782         // manual \tag
10783         tagSpan = buildCommon.makeSpan([], buildExpression$1(tag, options, true), options);
10784       }
10785 
10786       tagSpan.depth = rw.depth;
10787       tagSpan.height = rw.height;
10788       tagSpans.push({
10789         type: "elem",
10790         elem: tagSpan,
10791         shift
10792       });
10793     }
10794   }
10795 
10796   for (c = 0, colDescrNum = 0; // Continue while either there are more columns or more column
10797   // descriptions, so trailing separators don't get lost.
10798   c < nc || colDescrNum < colDescriptions.length; ++c, ++colDescrNum) {
10799     var colDescr = colDescriptions[colDescrNum] || {};
10800     var firstSeparator = true;
10801 
10802     while (colDescr.type === "separator") {
10803       // If there is more than one separator in a row, add a space
10804       // between them.
10805       if (!firstSeparator) {
10806         colSep = buildCommon.makeSpan(["arraycolsep"], []);
10807         colSep.style.width = makeEm(options.fontMetrics().doubleRuleSep);
10808         cols.push(colSep);
10809       }
10810 
10811       if (colDescr.separator === "|" || colDescr.separator === ":") {
10812         var lineType = colDescr.separator === "|" ? "solid" : "dashed";
10813         var separator = buildCommon.makeSpan(["vertical-separator"], [], options);
10814         separator.style.height = makeEm(totalHeight);
10815         separator.style.borderRightWidth = makeEm(ruleThickness);
10816         separator.style.borderRightStyle = lineType;
10817         separator.style.margin = "0 " + makeEm(-ruleThickness / 2);
10818 
10819         var _shift = totalHeight - offset;
10820 
10821         if (_shift) {
10822           separator.style.verticalAlign = makeEm(-_shift);
10823         }
10824 
10825         cols.push(separator);
10826       } else {
10827         throw new ParseError("Invalid separator type: " + colDescr.separator);
10828       }
10829 
10830       colDescrNum++;
10831       colDescr = colDescriptions[colDescrNum] || {};
10832       firstSeparator = false;
10833     }
10834 
10835     if (c >= nc) {
10836       continue;
10837     }
10838 
10839     var sepwidth = void 0;
10840 
10841     if (c > 0 || group.hskipBeforeAndAfter) {
10842       sepwidth = utils.deflt(colDescr.pregap, arraycolsep);
10843 
10844       if (sepwidth !== 0) {
10845         colSep = buildCommon.makeSpan(["arraycolsep"], []);
10846         colSep.style.width = makeEm(sepwidth);
10847         cols.push(colSep);
10848       }
10849     }
10850 
10851     var col = [];
10852 
10853     for (r = 0; r < nr; ++r) {
10854       var row = body[r];
10855       var elem = row[c];
10856 
10857       if (!elem) {
10858         continue;
10859       }
10860 
10861       var _shift2 = row.pos - offset;
10862 
10863       elem.depth = row.depth;
10864       elem.height = row.height;
10865       col.push({
10866         type: "elem",
10867         elem: elem,
10868         shift: _shift2
10869       });
10870     }
10871 
10872     col = buildCommon.makeVList({
10873       positionType: "individualShift",
10874       children: col
10875     }, options);
10876     col = buildCommon.makeSpan(["col-align-" + (colDescr.align || "c")], [col]);
10877     cols.push(col);
10878 
10879     if (c < nc - 1 || group.hskipBeforeAndAfter) {
10880       sepwidth = utils.deflt(colDescr.postgap, arraycolsep);
10881 
10882       if (sepwidth !== 0) {
10883         colSep = buildCommon.makeSpan(["arraycolsep"], []);
10884         colSep.style.width = makeEm(sepwidth);
10885         cols.push(colSep);
10886       }
10887     }
10888   }
10889 
10890   body = buildCommon.makeSpan(["mtable"], cols); // Add \hline(s), if any.
10891 
10892   if (hlines.length > 0) {
10893     var line = buildCommon.makeLineSpan("hline", options, ruleThickness);
10894     var dashes = buildCommon.makeLineSpan("hdashline", options, ruleThickness);
10895     var vListElems = [{
10896       type: "elem",
10897       elem: body,
10898       shift: 0
10899     }];
10900 
10901     while (hlines.length > 0) {
10902       var hline = hlines.pop();
10903       var lineShift = hline.pos - offset;
10904 
10905       if (hline.isDashed) {
10906         vListElems.push({
10907           type: "elem",
10908           elem: dashes,
10909           shift: lineShift
10910         });
10911       } else {
10912         vListElems.push({
10913           type: "elem",
10914           elem: line,
10915           shift: lineShift
10916         });
10917       }
10918     }
10919 
10920     body = buildCommon.makeVList({
10921       positionType: "individualShift",
10922       children: vListElems
10923     }, options);
10924   }
10925 
10926   if (tagSpans.length === 0) {
10927     return buildCommon.makeSpan(["mord"], [body], options);
10928   } else {
10929     var eqnNumCol = buildCommon.makeVList({
10930       positionType: "individualShift",
10931       children: tagSpans
10932     }, options);
10933     eqnNumCol = buildCommon.makeSpan(["tag"], [eqnNumCol], options);
10934     return buildCommon.makeFragment([body, eqnNumCol]);
10935   }

10944 var mathmlBuilder$5 = function mathmlBuilder(group, options) {
10945   var tbl = [];
10946   var glue = new mathMLTree.MathNode("mtd", [], ["mtr-glue"]);
10947   var tag = new mathMLTree.MathNode("mtd", [], ["mml-eqn-num"]);
10948 
10949   for (var i = 0; i < group.body.length; i++) {
10950     var rw = group.body[i];
10951     var row = [];
10952 
10953     for (var j = 0; j < rw.length; j++) {
10954       row.push(new mathMLTree.MathNode("mtd", [buildGroup(rw[j], options)]));
10955     }
10956 
10957     if (group.tags && group.tags[i]) {
10958       row.unshift(glue);
10959       row.push(glue);
10960 
10961       if (group.leqno) {
10962         row.unshift(tag);
10963       } else {
10964         row.push(tag);
10965       }
10966     }
10967 
10968     tbl.push(new mathMLTree.MathNode("mtr", row));
10969   }
10970 
10971   var table = new mathMLTree.MathNode("mtable", tbl); // Set column alignment, row spacing, column spacing, and
10972   // array lines by setting attributes on the table element.
10973   // Set the row spacing. In MathML, we specify a gap distance.
10974   // We do not use rowGap[] because MathML automatically increases
10975   // cell height with the height/depth of the element content.
10976   // LaTeX \arraystretch multiplies the row baseline-to-baseline distance.
10977   // We simulate this by adding (arraystretch - 1)em to the gap. This
10978   // does a reasonable job of adjusting arrays containing 1 em tall content.
10979   // The 0.16 and 0.09 values are found empirically. They produce an array
10980   // similar to LaTeX and in which content does not interfere with \hlines.
10981 
10982   var gap = group.arraystretch === 0.5 ? 0.1 // {smallmatrix}, {subarray}
10983   : 0.16 + group.arraystretch - 1 + (group.addJot ? 0.09 : 0);
10984   table.setAttribute("rowspacing", makeEm(gap)); // MathML table lines go only between cells.
10985   // To place a line on an edge we'll use <menclose>, if necessary.
10986 
10987   var menclose = "";
10988   var align = "";
10989 
10990   if (group.cols && group.cols.length > 0) {
10991     // Find column alignment, column spacing, and  vertical lines.
10992     var cols = group.cols;
10993     var columnLines = "";
10994     var prevTypeWasAlign = false;
10995     var iStart = 0;
10996     var iEnd = cols.length;
10997 
10998     if (cols[0].type === "separator") {
10999       menclose += "top ";
11000       iStart = 1;
11001     }
11002 
11003     if (cols[cols.length - 1].type === "separator") {
11004       menclose += "bottom ";
11005       iEnd -= 1;
11006     }
11007 
11008     for (var _i = iStart; _i < iEnd; _i++) {
11009       if (cols[_i].type === "align") {
11010         align += alignMap[cols[_i].align];
11011 
11012         if (prevTypeWasAlign) {
11013           columnLines += "none ";
11014         }
11015 
11016         prevTypeWasAlign = true;
11017       } else if (cols[_i].type === "separator") {
11018         // MathML accepts only single lines between cells.
11019         // So we read only the first of consecutive separators.
11020         if (prevTypeWasAlign) {
11021           columnLines += cols[_i].separator === "|" ? "solid " : "dashed ";
11022           prevTypeWasAlign = false;
11023         }
11024       }
11025     }
11026 
11027     table.setAttribute("columnalign", align.trim());
11028 
11029     if (/[sd]/.test(columnLines)) {
11030       table.setAttribute("columnlines", columnLines.trim());
11031     }
11032   } // Set column spacing.
11033 
11034 
11035   if (group.colSeparationType === "align") {
11036     var _cols = group.cols || [];
11037 
11038     var spacing = "";
11039 
11040     for (var _i2 = 1; _i2 < _cols.length; _i2++) {
11041       spacing += _i2 % 2 ? "0em " : "1em ";
11042     }
11043 
11044     table.setAttribute("columnspacing", spacing.trim());
11045   } else if (group.colSeparationType === "alignat" || group.colSeparationType === "gather") {
11046     table.setAttribute("columnspacing", "0em");
11047   } else if (group.colSeparationType === "small") {
11048     table.setAttribute("columnspacing", "0.2778em");
11049   } else if (group.colSeparationType === "CD") {
11050     table.setAttribute("columnspacing", "0.5em");
11051   } else {
11052     table.setAttribute("columnspacing", "1em");
11053   } // Address \hline and \hdashline
11054 
11055 
11056   var rowLines = "";
11057   var hlines = group.hLinesBeforeRow;
11058   menclose += hlines[0].length > 0 ? "left " : "";
11059   menclose += hlines[hlines.length - 1].length > 0 ? "right " : "";
11060 
11061   for (var _i3 = 1; _i3 < hlines.length - 1; _i3++) {
11062     rowLines += hlines[_i3].length === 0 ? "none " // MathML accepts only a single line between rows. Read one element.
11063     : hlines[_i3][0] ? "dashed " : "solid ";
11064   }
11065 
11066   if (/[sd]/.test(rowLines)) {
11067     table.setAttribute("rowlines", rowLines.trim());
11068   }
11069 
11070   if (menclose !== "") {
11071     table = new mathMLTree.MathNode("menclose", [table]);
11072     table.setAttribute("notation", menclose.trim());
11073   }
11074 
11075   if (group.arraystretch && group.arraystretch < 1) {
11076     // A small array. Wrap in scriptstyle so row gap is not too large.
11077     table = new mathMLTree.MathNode("mstyle", [table]);
11078     table.setAttribute("scriptlevel", "1");
11079   }
11080 
11081   return table;
11082 }; // Convenience function for align, align*, aligned, alignat, alignat*, alignedat.
